headlines.description: — Myles Turner scored 28 points, Pascal Siakam added 26 and the Indiana Pacers beat the Detroit Pistons 111-100 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Turner scores 28 and Siakam has 26 to lead the Pacers past the Pistons, 111-100

headlines.description: — Devin Booker scored 37 points, Kevin Durant added 23 and the Phoenix Suns weathered a late rally in a 130-123 victory over the Washington Wizards on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Devin Booker scores 37 points, Suns survive scare to beat Wizards 130-123

events.name: Cleveland Cavaliers at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 40 points and eight assists in three quarters, and the Oklahoma City Thunder rolled past the Cleveland Cavaliers 134-114 on Thursday night in a matchup of teams with the best records in the NBA.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander scores 40 as Thunder roll past Cavaliers 134-114 in matchup of NBA leaders

events.name: LA Clippers at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 23 points, James Harden had 19 points and the Los Angeles Clippers beat the Portland Trail Blazers 118-89 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Norman Powell scores 23 points to help the Clippers beat the Trail Blazers 118-89

headlines.description: — DeMar DeRozan had 33 points, Malik Monk added 26 points and nine assists and the Sacramento Kings beat the Houston Rockets 132-127 on Thursday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: DeMar DeRozan scores 33 points, Malik Monk adds 26 in the Kings' 132-127 win over the Rockets
